baseName.name: baseName
baseName.description: Name of the Base Station assigned through the Wireless Network Administration Program.

baseNetworkName.name: baseNetworkName
baseNetworkName.description: Name of the Wireless Network containing the Base Station. This name has been assigned through the Wireless Network Administration Program.

baseAdminIPAddr.name: baseAdminIPAddr
baseAdminIPAddr.description: IP Address of the station housing the Wireless Network Administration Program.

wrBaseTable.name: wrBaseTable
wrBaseTable.description: This table contains wireless interface parameters and state variables, one entry per wireless interface.

wrBaseEntry.name: wrBaseEntry
wrBaseEntry.description: An entry contains wireless parameters and state variables for a particular interface.

baseIfIndex.name: baseIfIndex
baseIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the wireless interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the IfIndex object defined in MIB-II for the same interface.

baseHDLCaddress.name: baseHDLCaddress
baseHDLCaddress.description: HDLC address of the wireless interface.

baseNbOFRemote.name: baseNbOFRemote
baseNbOFRemote.description: Number of wireless workstations registered to the wireless interface.

baseCellIdentifier.name: baseCellIdentifier
baseCellIdentifier.description: Identifier of the cell controlled by the wireless interface.

baseEmittedPower.name: baseEmittedPower
baseEmittedPower.description: Emitted power of the wireless interface.

baseControllerCardDesc.name: baseControllerCardDesc
baseControllerCardDesc.description: Vital Product Data of the wireless controller card performing the wireless interface function.

baseUnivAddress.name: baseUnivAddress
baseUnivAddress.description: Universal address of the wireless controller card performing the wireless interface function.

baseModemDesc.name: baseModemDesc
baseModemDesc.description: Vital Product Data of the transceiver performing the wireless interface function.

baseTopologyTrapActive.name: baseTopologyTrapActive
baseTopologyTrapActive.description: Traps will be sent when wireless workstation registers to and deregisters from the wireless interface only if this object is set to active.

wrBaseStatsTable.name: wrBaseStatsTable
wrBaseStatsTable.description: This table contains wireless interface statistics, one entry per wireless interface.

wrBaseStatsEntry.name: wrBaseStatsEntry
wrBaseStatsEntry.description: An entry contains wireless statistics for a particular interface.

baseStatsIfIndex.name: baseStatsIfIndex
baseStatsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the wireless interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the IfIndex object defined in MIB-II for the same interface.

baseStatsXmit.name: baseStatsXmit
baseStatsXmit.description: Number of packets transmitted over the wireless interface.

baseStatsRxmit.name: baseStatsRxmit
baseStatsRxmit.description: Number of packets retransmitted over the wireless interface due to a lack of positive acknowledgement.

baseStatsNegAckRcv.name: baseStatsNegAckRcv
baseStatsNegAckRcv.description: Number of negative acknowledgement received over the wireless interface (workstations congestion indicator).

baseStatsRcv.name: baseStatsRcv
baseStatsRcv.description: Number of packets received over the wireless interface.

baseStatsLineErrors.name: baseStatsLineErrors
baseStatsLineErrors.description: Number of slots assigned to wireless workstations that fail to use or that fail to receive (HDLC error).

baseStatsNegAckXmit.name: baseStatsNegAckXmit
baseStatsNegAckXmit.description: Number of negative acknowledgement transmitted over the wireless interface (base congestion indicator).

baseStatsFramePurged.name: baseStatsFramePurged
baseStatsFramePurged.description: Number of frames that were purged by the wireless interface because they were corrupted during air transmission.

baseStatsFreqDelete.name: baseStatsFreqDelete
baseStatsFreqDelete.description: Number of times a single frequency had to be replaced in the frequency hopping pattern because an excessive level of interference was detected for that frequency.

baseStatsHopAdvance.name: baseStatsHopAdvance
baseStatsHopAdvance.description: Number of times a hop advance procedure had to be performed because an excessive level of interference was detected for each frequency of the hopping pattern.

baseStatsCLineErrors.name: baseStatsCLineErrors
baseStatsCLineErrors.description: Number of times the first packet of a frame was received over the wireless interface with an HDLC error.

baseStatsRcvICRFrame.name: baseStatsRcvICRFrame
baseStatsRcvICRFrame.description: Number of frames received by the base station on the wireless interface that must be forwarded to one or more wireless workstations registered to the same wireless interface.

baseStatsXmitICRFrame.name: baseStatsXmitICRFrame
baseStatsXmitICRFrame.description: Number of frames forwarded by the base station from a wireless workstation to another one. This counter may be incremented several times for the same frame if it is a broadcast frame.

baseStatsNoICRBufferAvail.name: baseStatsNoICRBufferAvail
baseStatsNoICRBufferAvail.description: Number of frames received on the wireless interface coming from a wireless workstation and going to another wireless workstation registered to the same wireless interface that had to be discarded due to a lack of resources.

baseStatsNotRoutedICRFrame.name: baseStatsNotRoutedICRFrame
baseStatsNotRoutedICRFrame.description: Number of frames received on the wireless interface coming from a wireless workstation and going to another wireless workstation that were discarded because the target wireless workstation could not be found.

baseStatsNbCUserEst.name: baseStatsNbCUserEst
baseStatsNbCUserEst.description: Number of wireless workstation trying to transmit in C interval.

wrRemoteTable.name: wrRemoteTable
wrRemoteTable.description: This table contains management information for the wireless workstations registered to the wireless interfaces, one entry per registered wireless workstation.

wrRemoteEntry.name: wrRemoteEntry
wrRemoteEntry.description: An entry contains management information for a particular wireless workstation. An object of this type is transient in that it ceases to exist when (or soon after) the wireless workstation deregisters from the base.

remIfIndex.name: remIfIndex
remIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the wireless interface to which is registered the workstation for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the IfIndex object defined in MIB-II for the same interface.

remIndex.name: remIndex
remIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the registered wireless workstation for which this entry contains management information. This value has been dynamically assigned to the wireless workstation when it registered to the base.

remMacAddress.name: remMacAddress
remMacAddress.description: MAC address of the wireless workstation.

remControllerCardDesc.name: remControllerCardDesc
remControllerCardDesc.description: Adapter Vital Product Data of the wireless workstation.

remUnivAddress.name: remUnivAddress
remUnivAddress.description: Universal address of the wireless workstation.

remModemDesc.name: remModemDesc
remModemDesc.description: Transceiver Vital Product Data of the wireless workstation.

wrRemoteStatsTable.name: wrRemoteStatsTable
wrRemoteStatsTable.description: This table contains statistics information for the wireless workstations registered to the wireless interfaces, one entry per registered wireless workstation.

wrRemStatsEntry.name: wrRemStatsEntry
wrRemStatsEntry.description: An entry contains statistics information for a particular wireless workstation. An object of this type is transient in that it ceases to exist when (or soon after) the wireless workstation deregisters from the base.

remStatsIfIndex.name: remStatsIfIndex
remStatsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the wireless interface to which is registered the workstation for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the IfIndex object defined in MIB-II for the same interface.

remStatsIndex.name: remStatsIndex
remStatsIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the wireless workstation for which this entry contains statistics information. This value has been dynamically assigned to the wireless workstation when it registered to the base.

remStatsXmit.name: remStatsXmit
remStatsXmit.description: Number of packets transmitted over the wireless interface to this particular wireless workstation.

remStatsRxmit.name: remStatsRxmit
remStatsRxmit.description: Number of packets retried over the wireless interface due to a lack of positive acknowledgement from this particular wireless workstation.

remStatsNegAckRcv.name: remStatsNegAckRcv
remStatsNegAckRcv.description: Number of Out of Sequences Packets received over the wireless interface from this particular wireless workstation.

remStatsRcv.name: remStatsRcv
remStatsRcv.description: Number of packets received over the wireless interface from this particular wireless workstation.

remStatsLineErrors.name: remStatsLineErrors
remStatsLineErrors.description: Number of slots assigned to this particular wireless workstation that fail to use or that fail to receive (HDLC error).

remStatsNegAckXmit.name: remStatsNegAckXmit
remStatsNegAckXmit.description: Number of negative acknowledgement transmitted to a given workstation over the wireless interface (base congestion indicator).
